    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is a museum-quality 2004 BMW M3 (E46), a definitive example of high-revving naturally aspirated engineering. At its heart is the S54 3.2L inline-six, utilizing individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system that pulls cleanly to its 8,000 RPM redline. This specimen has undergone comprehensive preventative maintenance, including documented rod bearing replacement and a full VANOS overhaul. The chassis integrity is guaranteed by a reinforced rear subframe, a critical upgrade for this platform. Power is managed via a precise Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and a factory variable M differential lock, ensuring optimal torque distribution. The suspension geometry remains true, featuring refreshed bushings and OEM-spec dampers for that signature communicative feedback. The exterior retains its factory-original finish with no evidence of panel replacement or paint correction. This is a mechanically synchronized, collector-grade machine for the discerning driver who values technical perfection.",
      "price": 44500.0,
